---
// src/pages/about.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Me | Bê Acosta" description="Bettina (Bê) Acosta - Senior Technical PM researching agentic commerce, semantic search, and e-commerce architectures.">
  <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-mono); margin-bottom: 2rem; border: none; padding: 0;">
    ℹ️ about_me_
  </h1>

  <section class="about-content">
    <p>
      Hi, I'm <strong>Bettina (Bê) Acosta</strong> (aka <strong>@britneyscripts</strong>). 👋
    </p>
    <p>
      I'm a <strong>Senior Technical Product Manager</strong> with 8+ years leading digital products and e-commerce infrastructure across Latin America. Right now, I'm researching <strong>agentic commerce</strong> for my Data Science MBA at USP (ICMC)—specifically, how AI agents discover, read, evaluate, and recommend products.
    </p>
    <p>
      On Twitter/X, I'm @britneyscripts. The name stuck after years of writing automation scripts and realizing I needed a handle that didn't take itself too seriously.
    </p>

    <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border); margin: 2rem 0;" />

    <h3>👻 What I'm working on: Ghostprod</h3>
    <p>
      I'm building <strong>Ghostprod</strong>: an open-source, multi-agent pipeline measuring the <strong>Semantic Invisibility</strong> of e-commerce Product Detail Pages (PDPs). 
    </p>
    <p>
      It is my MBA thesis instrument. It is also the answer to a question nobody was asking yet: <em>when agents replace search bars, which e-commerce sites disappear first?</em> We evaluate PDPs across three core pillars: web performance (CrUX), semantic markup (Schema.org), and NLP-parseability.
    </p>

    <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border); margin: 2rem 0;" />

    <h3>🛠️ The stack I'm working with</h3>
    <p>
      I don't have funding for enterprise-grade research infrastructure. I have: <strong>Antigravity IDE, Gemini, Google AI Studio, GCP credits, BigQuery, Dataform, Python everywhere, local vector DBs (ChromaDB), and a USP student account.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      It's enough. Verifiable data beats marketing gloss.
    </p>

    <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border); margin: 2rem 0;" />

    <h3>✍️ Why this blog exists</h3>
    <p>
      I needed a space outside <strong>LinkedIn's</strong> and Substack's closed gardens. Somewhere I could publish <strong>indexed, searchable content</strong> that appears when someone searches for "agent readiness" or "SEO for AI agents". 
    </p>
    <p>
      This blog is a tribute to the old days—like running a WordPress site on localhost, but modernized. It is static, ultra-fast, and compiles Markdown directly from my Obsidian vault.
    </p>

    <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border); margin: 2rem 0;" />

    <h3>🔗 Connect</h3>
    <ul style="list-style: none; margin-left: 0; margin-top: 1rem;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">🐦 <strong>Twitter/X:</strong> <a href="https://twitter.com/britneyscripts" target="_blank">@britneyscripts</a></li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">💼 <strong>LinkedIn:</strong> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/" target="_blank">Bettina Acosta de Paula</a></li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">💻 <strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/britneyscripts" target="_blank">@britneyscripts</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
